Most female users fall into the low usage categories (usage <= 2).
We see an upward trend between miles and income.

Insights and Reccomendations¶

Customer Profile:

  • There are more male customers than females and more partnered customers than single.
  • There are more partnered people in high income categories.
  • The TM195 is the most common treadmill overall.
  • The TM195 and TM498 were mostly used by low to middle income users and was associated with lower usage.
  • The TM798 was most popular among high income users and was associated with high usage.
  • Wealthier people tend to have higher perceived fitness and higher expected treadmill miles.
  • Perceived fitness tends to be pretty constant regarless of age, but increases with education.

Based on my analysis, these are the key insights and reccomendations for targeting new customers:

  • The key type of customer to target is single females in order to expand the customer base.
    • Since over 75% of customers expect to use the treadmill for less than 200 miles, an affordable option tailored to single people could be a useful addition.
  • The TM498 treadmill has similar users to the TM195, but the TM195 is more popular.
    • Since the TM195 is dominant for miles between 0 and 100, the TM498 treadmill could be used to target lower income groups looking for more miles in the 100-200 miles range, as they may not be able to afford the TM798.
    • There are much less people in the high income categories associated with the TM798, so products for lower income categories are more important.
  • 50% of customers have education between 14 and 16 years, the median age is 26, and perceived fitness increases with age.
    • It is important to target yonger users who have lower perceived fitness, particularly in the fitness = 2-3 range.
